page.title: 03BOURNEMOUTH
page.content:
Bournemouth is a seaside town on the south coast of England in the county of Dorset.It is a holiday and residential town with a population of over 150,000 people. Bournemouth is a modern town,a late developer which became fashionable more recently than many of its rivals. In fact,less than two centuries ago the area was nothing but a solitary stretch of sheltered dunes bordered by sandstone cliffs,and where smuggling was rife. It is said that Captain Lewis Tregonwell is the founder of Bournemouth. Bourneouth, now has miles and miles of clean sandy beaches and the bay is sheltered by the Purbeck hills to the west and Hengistbury Head to the east.
Andrew Mullet
